wiki.content: "mad woman" is the twelfth track from Taylor Swift's eighth studio album "folklore". It was released on July 24, 2020, through Republic Records. This song was confirmed on Taylor’s social media accounts on July 23, 2020. Much like her previous songs “Blank Space” and “Look What You Made Me Do,” which she references throughout the song, Swift connects the concept of a delusional woman to her personal life, particularly her battles with Scooter Braun and Scott Borchetta over owning her music and rapper Kanye West after he defamed her on his song “Famous.” Some of the story may originate from Rebekah Harkness, who Swift based earlier "folklore track" “the last great american dynasty” on. “mad woman” debuted at #47 on the Billboard Hot 100 during the chart week of August 8, 2020.
